  m_Name: FirInfo
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::PlantInfoData
  plantName: Fir Tree
  description: Fir trees are evergreen conifers in the genus Abies (family Pinaceae),
    known for their soft, flat needles that attach individually to branches, leaving
    a smooth surface when they fall. They are characterized by a narrow, conical
    shape, upright cones that sit like candles, and resinous bark. Firs are popular
    as Christmas trees, such as the balsam or Fraser fir.
  plantImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 7005e172d1c14b34f8e548ff93f46755, type: 3}
